                        <h3>
                            General rules and Regulations after admission
                        </h3>

                        <br>



                        <p>
                            The new- batch will be welcomed by the senior students and staff in an amicable manner. Raging is strictly prohibited and if done punishable. On the other hand new-comers welcome function will be arranged to get familiarised with all and the Institution.
                            Students are expected to maintain dignity and to behave with discipline to maintain the high standard of medical profession.
                            It is mandatory to wear uniform, which will be provided from Institute on payment. Uniform should be kept neat and tidy. Male students should use black shoes; female students can use simple ear studs only in the class or on duty. They are not permitted to wear other ornaments.
                            Students are expected to be regular and punctual in the classes and should maintain a minimum of 80% attendance as required by the Para Medical Board. Students are permitted to go on leave only in the declared holidays. In case of emergency, including medical, proper intimation is to be provided.
                            Mobile phones use and possession in the class and within the Institute is prohibited.
                            Students shouldn`t organize any parties, tours, or get together without the knowledge of the Principal/course in charge.
                        </p>






